snippet.title: Update: Police issue Amber Alert for 5-year-old allegedly abducted by 3 men
snippet.description:

Police have delivered an Amber Alert after a 5-year-old girl was reportedly  by three men in Texas, bestowing to reports.
ABC News say the vigilant for Maleah Davis of Houston was issued on May 5. The girl was last seen wearing a blue zip-up jacket, blue jeans, running shoe, and a pink curtsy in her hair.
Maleah‚Äôs stepfather, 26-year-old Darion Vence, says that three men beaten him before taking the girl and leaving he and his 2-year-old son behind.
Reports claim that Maleah was last seen at around 9 p.m. on Saturday night, at the same time as the three unidentified males are thought to be driving a 2010 blue Chevrolet truck. The license number for the vehicle has not been revealed, but the accused were spotted last on the Southwest Freeway near State Highway 6 in Sugar Land, around 20 miles south of Houston.



Houston Police
Twitted..
Better quality, color photo taken by traffic camera of the stolen Nissan Altima with tags 330-92G9.

Sgt. Mark Holbrook of the Houston Police Department set that Vence said he was in and out of mindfulness during the incident. At one point he woke up to find the suspects driving him and the two children around in a blue pickup

snippet.title: Weather Radio EAS #170 (Child Abduction Emergency)
snippet.description:
Amber Alert issued for 17 year old Faith Threet last night. 

A missing 17-year-old from Robertson County was found Saturday morning. Faith Treet, 17, went missing Thursday and was last seen with 44-year-old Kevin Dennis Pitt. The Robertson County Sheriff‚Äôs Office said investigators are working with the District Attorney‚Äôs Office regarding upcoming charges against Pitt.

Just a day after an Endangered Child Alert was released, the Tennessee Bureau of Investigation has put out an AMBER Alert for a 17-year-old from Robertson County.


Officials say Faith Threet may be with 44-year-old Kevin Dennis Pitt in the area of Adairville, KY. Pitt is wanted in Robertson County for failure to appear on multiple charges.

Faith was last seen in the area of Cowan Road in Springfield, Tenn. around 3 p.m. Thursday.

Update: Faith has been found safe and Kevin Pitt is in custody

snippet.description: Today, we're covering the true scary story of Amber Tuccaro. To this day, her mysterious death remains an unsolved mystery. What happened to Amber Tuccaro after her chilling last phone call? In the phone call, you can faintly hear her killer's voice as he led her further out into the middle of nowhere. Although Amber Tuccaro was eventually found murdered and a slew of evidence was left behind, investigators were still unable to pin the crime on any suspect. The investigation by detectives led no results. Internet sleuths across the web have listened to the phone call again and again searching for any clues to no avail. Will this true crime case ever be solved? Join us for a true crime storytime covering the unsolved cold case of Amber Tuccaro.
